[normal] the committee
[normal] as it draws on 
[normal]our particular knowledge
[normal] base
[normal] 
[normal]with res
[normal]pect to
[normal] district 
[normal]energy
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]District Energy systems are systems that produce hot or chilled water at a central source for distribution through a network of below ground
[normal] pre-
[normal] insulated pipework to consumers connected to the energy network system. W
[normal]hilst the term community energy has been used in the past to mean district energy, it is now only used to refer to local energy systems of any type that have been implemented by community groups.                                                             
[normal]                            
