[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Addendum 2 – Cost Savings[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Operational cost savings are a typical benefit for district energy consumers, when compared to conventional sources of energy.  These cost savings vary f
[normal]rom scheme to scheme but energy supplies are often benchmarked to show savings in the region of 5%-10%, when compared to the all-in costs of operation and maintenance of typical boiler plant.  
[normal]As an example of the scale of these cost savings, the total 
[normal]savings for all consumers connected to the Southampton District energy Scheme are estimated to be approximately £500,000 per annum.
[normal]The consumer cost savings already achieved at a number of UKDEA members’ schemes have been used as a benchmark, to provide p
[normal]rojected cost savings to consumers of future district energy schemes.  In line with this paper’s projections for future delivery of district energy, the annual operational cost savings are shown in the chart below, with an estimate of the public sectors sa
[normal]vings also shown separately on the same chart.
